
Overview of verb persist

The verb persist has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (11) prevail, persist, die hard, run, endure -- (continue to exist; "These stories die hard"; "The legend of Elvis endures")
2. (8) persevere, persist, hang in, hang on, hold on -- (be persistent, refuse to stop; "he persisted to call me every night"; "The child persisted and kept asking questions")
